  "prompt": "What is the best apps for learning how to sing english songs with audio check?",
  "response": "Learning to sing English songs can be a fun and rewarding experience, especially when using apps that provide audio feedback and guidance. Here are some of the best apps for learning how to sing English songs with audio check:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Smule (Sing Karaoke)**\n- **Features**: Smule is a popular karaoke app that lets you sing along with popular English songs. It provides real-time feedback on pitch, rhythm, and timing. You can also duet with other users or professional singers.\n- **Why It\u2019s Great**: The app offers a wide range of songs and a social community for motivation.\n\n---\n\n### **2. SingTrue (iOS)**\n- **Features**: SingTrue helps you learn to sing in tune by providing personalized exercises and real-time feedback on your pitch accuracy.\n- **Why It\u2019s Great**: It\u2019s beginner-friendly and focuses on building your musical ear and vocal skills.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Vanido (iOS)**\n- **Features**: Vanido offers daily vocal exercises tailored to your skill level. It provides real-time feedback on pitch and helps you improve your singing technique.\n- **Why It\u2019s Great**: The app is designed to make singing practice fun and consistent.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Yousician**\n- **Features**: Yousician offers singing lessons with real-time feedback on pitch and rhythm. It includes a large library of songs to practice with.\n- **Why It\u2019s Great**: The app is interactive and suitable for all skill levels, from beginners to advanced singers.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Sing & See**\n- **Features**: Sing & See is a professional vocal training software that provides visual feedback on pitch, vibrato, and other vocal aspects. It\u2019s available for both desktop and mobile.\n- **Why It\u2019s Great**: It\u2019s ideal for singers who want in-depth feedback and analysis of their vocal performance.\n\n---\n\n### **6. SingSharp**\n- **Features**: SingSharp offers vocal training exercises and karaoke-style singing with real-time feedback on pitch accuracy. It also has a pitch detection feature to help you improve.\n- **Why It\u2019s Great**: The app is easy to use and offers a variety of songs and exercises.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Vocalizr**\n- **Features**: Vocalizr provides vocal exercises and lessons with pitch correction and real-time feedback. It focuses on improving your vocal range and control.\n- **Why It\u2019s Great**: The app is great for singers who want to focus on technique and accuracy.\n\n---\n\n### **8. StarMaker (Karaoke & Singing)**\n- **Features**: StarMaker allows you to sing along with popular English songs and provides feedback on pitch and rhythm. It also includes vocal effects and a social community.\n- **Why It\u2019s Great**: The app is user-friendly and offers a wide selection of songs.\n\n---\n\n### **9. Pitch Analyzer**\n- **Features**: This app analyzes your pitch and provides feedback on how well you\u2019re hitting the notes. It\u2019s useful for practicing both singing and playing instruments.\n- **Why It\u2019s Great**: It\u2019s a simple tool for improving pitch accuracy.\n\n---\n\n### **10. Singing Lessons by Singeo (iOS/Android)**\n- **Features**: This app offers step-by-step singing lessons, including exercises for pitch, breathing, and vocal control. It also provides feedback on your performance.\n- **Why It\u2019s Great**: It\u2019s a comprehensive app for beginners and intermediate singers.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Choosing the Right App**:\n- **For Beginners**: Start with apps like SingTrue or Vanido to build foundational skills.\n- **For Karaoke Lovers**: Smule and StarMaker are great for singing along with popular songs.\n- **For Serious Training**: Sing & See or Vocalizr offer more advanced feedback and analysis.\n\nChoose an app that aligns with your goals and enjoy the journey of improving your singing skills!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
